♪ You know, when my heart
lets its guard down, it wants to be weak ♪

1305
01:26:02,232 --> 01:26:03,475
Shinichi...

1306
01:26:03,499 --> 01:26:09,308
♪ You know, when my heart
lets its guard down, it wants to be weak ♪

1307
01:26:09,332 --> 01:26:25,841
♪ so, yes, I gritted my teeth
and tried putting on a forced smile ♪

1308
01:26:25,865 --> 01:26:29,141
♪ I want to see you, right now ♪

1309
01:26:29,165 --> 01:26:32,242
red or blue?

1310
01:26:32,266 --> 01:26:33,698
I want to see you, right now
Red, I guess?

1311
01:26:34,087 --> 01:26:38,598
And look! Both Shinichi and I
have red as our lucky color for May!

1312
01:26:38,787 --> 01:26:39,908
I want to see you
So I decided that we gotta see this!

1313
01:26:39,932 --> 01:26:41,598
So I decided that we gotta see this!

1314
01:26:52,813 --> 01:26:54,969
Ran! Ran! You alright?!

1315
01:26:55,695 --> 01:26:57,217
Damn! She can't hear me!

1316
01:26:57,565 --> 01:26:59,241
Oh, yeah!
My cell phone!

1317
01:26:59,396 --> 01:27:00,343
It's gone!

1318
01:27:00,367 --> 01:27:02,587
Damn, did I drop it earlier?!

1319
01:27:02,612 --> 01:27:04,612
T-there's a little boy here!

1320
01:27:06,394 --> 01:27:09,242
You're safe now,
little boy! Let's go!

1321
01:27:09,266 --> 01:27:14,375
W-wait! There are still
people trapped inside!

1322
01:27:14,399 --> 01:27:15,732
Alright, wait here!

1323
01:27:18,718 --> 01:27:20,660
It's no use!
Get the jackhammer!

1324
01:27:20,685 --> 01:27:21,519
Right!

1325
01:27:22,486 --> 01:27:24,653
Today's my wedding anniversary,

1326
01:27:24,678 --> 01:27:27,311
but it doesn't look like
I'll be enjoying it much...

1327
01:27:28,798 --> 01:27:32,499
"I gave you three minutes!
Enjoy it all you can!"

1328
01:27:33,365 --> 01:27:38,933
I get it! He was telling me
to enjoy three minutes of my birthday!

1329
01:27:40,198 --> 01:27:42,674
Wait! Wasn't that when-

1330
01:27:42,698 --> 01:27:45,774
Oh, that sounds like fun!

1331
01:27:45,798 --> 01:27:48,575
I take it you've already
gotten him a present?

1332
01:27:48,599 --> 01:27:50,774
No, on Saturday
I'm going to-

1333
01:27:50,798 --> 01:27:54,441
He and I both like
the color red!

1334
01:27:54,465 --> 01:27:57,499
And we both have red
as our lucky color for May!

1335
01:27:57,931 --> 01:28:00,174
Lucky color?

1336
01:28:00,198 --> 01:28:01,332
Oh no!

1337
01:28:03,332 --> 01:28:05,274
Run, little boy!

1338
01:28:05,298 --> 01:28:07,707
- Little boy!
- Ran! The red one's a trap!

1339
01:28:07,731 --> 01:28:09,707
Cut the blue one!
Don't cut the red one!

1340
01:28:09,731 --> 01:28:11,865
Ran, where are you?! Respond!

1341
01:28:21,032 --> 01:28:23,774
Ran! Ran! Ran!

1342
01:28:23,798 --> 01:28:25,399
Ran!

1343
01:28:43,931 --> 01:28:46,941
Goodbye, Shinichi...

1344
01:28:46,965 --> 01:28:47,865
Ran!

1345
01:29:22,831 --> 01:29:24,965
I-impossible!

1346
01:29:44,765 --> 01:29:49,441
It's so wonderful that Ran-kun
is all right, Mori-kun!

1347
01:29:49,465 --> 01:29:51,375
Yes! Thank you!

1348
01:29:51,399 --> 01:29:53,174
- I'm with Nichiuri TV!
- Give us your thoughts!

1349
01:29:53,198 --> 01:29:55,174
What role did the great detective play?!

1350
01:29:55,198 --> 01:30:01,475
These bombings were meant
to tarnish my name as a great detective

1351
01:30:01,499 --> 01:30:04,731
by leading my daughter Ran
into a trap that-

1352
01:30:07,765 --> 01:30:08,765
Oh!

1353
01:30:12,399 --> 01:30:16,141
Conan-kun! You came
because you were worried?

1354
01:30:16,165 --> 01:30:17,674
Yeah...

1355
01:30:17,698 --> 01:30:19,807
Where'd you get that bandage?

1356
01:30:19,831 --> 01:30:21,475
Oh, I just fell...

1357
01:30:21,499 --> 01:30:23,707
You need to be careful.

1358
01:30:23,731 --> 01:30:26,641
Say, Conan-kun.
Have you seen Shinichi?

1359
01:30:26,665 --> 01:30:29,575
Huh? He was just here a minute ago...

1360
01:30:29,599 --> 01:30:32,575
Ugh! After I went
and got him a present...

1361
01:30:32,599 --> 01:30:36,341
Come to think of it,
Shinichi-niichan did seem puzzled!

1362
01:30:36,365 --> 01:30:39,575
He thought you'd pick
the red wire for sure,

1363
01:30:39,599 --> 01:30:43,008
so he was wondering
why you cut the blue one instead...

1364
01:30:43,032 --> 01:30:45,698
I didn't want to cut it.

1365
01:30:46,831 --> 01:30:48,141
"Legend of the Red Thread"

1366
01:30:48,165 --> 01:30:49,475
"Legend of the Red Thread"
After all, Shinichi and I...

1367
01:30:49,499 --> 01:30:52,308
After all, Shinichi and I...

1368
01:30:52,332 --> 01:30:54,499
...might be connected!

1369
